What you need to know:

When Madrid signed Benzema from Lyon for 40 million euros in 2009, the club's president Florentino Perez thought he was a mix of Zidane and Brazil's Ronaldo, both former 'Galacticos'.Gradually his image was downgraded, the perception of a thrilling, young talent morphing into something less exciting, a team player to be relied on rather than celebrated.